social_posts.post_text:
@solanoresources Tigercat 632E skidder hauling 35,000lbs of freshly felled timber down from the cut block
—
You know she means business in the woods with all four tires chained up and a grapple that big to grab a mitt full of timber

What comes to mind when office folk wish me a “happy hump day” every Wednesday of the week
—
@thebasementchad coming over the dirt mound at the helm of his beloved D375a-8

@borgergroup D8T on topsoil relocation duty. Earthworks projects typically kickoff with topsoil stripping and stockpiling, this fertile soil is important to preserve and used in later phases of the project to dress land for re-establishment of vegetation
—
This D8 is one of the sharper looking Cat’s I’ve seen in a while, there is something to be said for keeping iron in a clean and straight order

@mainlandconstructionmaterials primary production loader, a Cat 992 NG, loading out muck to a fleet of 775 rigid frames
—
Aggregate products for roads, buildings, schools, bridges, railways, concrete, asphalt, ocean ports, and your home garden begin their journey here at Mainland’s Cox quarry. The significance of aggregate products in our daily lives is insane!

@kpcldirtmovers 374D LME loading out 745 wiggle wagons. The LME spec machines came fitted with a slightly longer undercarriage (L), short stick & boom (ME), and of course a big bucket
—
After a bit of rain, the trucks were cycling up top due unfavourable wet conditions below, resulting in the 374 stretching down and top loading the wiggles. It ain’t always textbook loading setups when you have weather to deal with 🤷🏼‍♂️

@kpcldirtmovers D9T trimming the cut floor between haul trucks. When paired with a production excavator big dozers typically rip material ahead of the excavator, clean up the floor, or bulk push material to the production machine
—
Nothing says Saskatchewan like triple shank rippers on a D9!

@kpcldirtmovers 374D loading out 745 ADT’s (articulated dump trucks) on a fine Saskatchewan afternoon
—
Equally spaced trucks shipped off with dirt spilling over the edge is a thing of beauty

@priestlydemolition making 10 stories of concrete and rebar disappear in downtown Calgary!
—
While the Kobelco SK1600D handles floors 8 up to the roof (+ penthouse), a Case CX460 with 98ft Jewell high reach and Komatsu PC490 with 12,000lb Epiroc processor tackle the lower part of the building

Why walk the machine to the fuel farm when you can bring the fuel and lube + technicians to the machine?
—
@surewayconstructiongroup 385C getting its daily fuel top up, fully greased, and all fluids checked on a mass grading site in Alberta

If it ain’t spillin’, you ain’t fillin’
—
@kpcldirtmovers 775 loaded out of the cut with good clay fill to be used in the core/key trench of a perimeter dyke

@borgergroup new Hitachi EX1200-7 on its morning commute to work
—
With enough room for a party of 10 up top the catwalk, it’s hard to believe this is one of Hitachi’s smaller backhoes in their lineup, largest being an EX8000!

@badassclassroom having his usual fun hauling big equipment about in the Northern reaches of Alberta. In this case it was @heavymetalequipmentandrentals Hitachi EX1200, fully dressed of course.
—
Legend has it there ain’t no piece of heavy equipment he won’t put on a trailer and haul
